- Typical count, in this context, refers to the average number of wickets taken;
- 'Dismissals' is synonymous with 'wickets taken' indicating the number of times bowlers dismissed a batsman in a match.

sql:
SELECT bowler_id, COUNT(match_id) AS match_count
FROM match_bowling_stats
GROUP BY bowler_id;

SELECT DISTINCT b.name, b.nationality
FROM bowlers b
INNER JOIN match_bowling_stats mbs ON b.bowler_id = mbs.bowler_id;
